        "created_at": "2025-07-23T14:00:48.351Z",
        "cooked": "<p>the “contact updated their name” has LTR alignment, as if it’s a bidi paragraph with the name on-phone (<code>1</code>) being in English, even when that’s not the case (in this case, the contact name on-phone is entirely in Hebrew). that shouldn’t matter in my opinion though, i believe that regardless of which characterset is used for 1, 2 and 3, when in Hebrew the text should always be:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>א1</code> שינה/שינתה את שם הפרופיל שלו/שלה מ<code>ב2</code> ל<code>ג3</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>where א1 is the on-phone name, ב2 is the old Signal display name, and ג3 is the new Signal display name. <span class=\"spoiler\">Discourse sure doesn’t love it when i mix Hebrew and English… forces absolutely anything to be left-aligned.</span></p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/b/7/b701e5ad156c5bf92b3184bd5439bf1b3acd0054.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/b701e5ad156c5bf92b3184bd5439bf1b3acd0054\" title=\"Screenshot_20250723-154654_Signal\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/b/7/b701e5ad156c5bf92b3184bd5439bf1b3acd0054.jpeg\" alt=\"Screenshot_20250723-154654_Signal\" data-base62-sha1=\"q6Xro8ZdR3TJm3V1v2INzR6Cd9y\" width=\"690\" height=\"249\" data-dominant-color=\"B3ABAD\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot_20250723-154654_Signal</span><span class=\"informations\">719×260 25.5 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>",
